The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Missing chopper found
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Missing chopper found
                            
	Khammam, Andhra Pradesh, Nov. 13 (PTI): The wreckage of a helicopter that went missing three months ago after taking off from Hyderabad was today found in a remote area in Khammam district but there was no word on the fate of the four persons who were on board.        
	The remnants of the helicopter and identity cards of two persons on board were found on a hillock by a farmer, district police chief Mahesh Bhagwat said.        
	He said there was no information about the four persons  two pilots and two technical staff  who were in the chopper.        
	He said it was a difficult journey to the spot because of the terrain but added that more details would be available by tomorrow evening.        
	The Bell-430 helicopter of Ran Air, hired by the Chhattisgarh government, went missing on August 3 after taking off from Hyderabad.        
	All efforts to trace the helicopter failed despite help from the air force, prompting the Chhattisgarh government to announce a cash reward of Rs 10 lakh for any clues.                                                                                                                                                                         
